      <dsc>
         <c id="ref11" level="item">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Vol. 1: Napoleon Bonaparte as General in Chief: Portraits and Autographs</unittitle>
               <container altrender="Paige 15"
                          containerid="39002042582867"
                          id="aspace_ref11_c1"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_5235ba6a92a567249511bfca982c39c1">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This volume contains two manuscripts, both signed by Napoleon, and dated 1793 and 1795. There are 36 prints, all portraying Napoleon as he looked while serving as general in chief of the French army, from 1793 to 1798.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref13" level="item">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Vol. 2: Napoleon Bonaparte as First Consul: Portraits and Autographs</unittitle>
               <container altrender="Paige 15"
                          containerid="39002042582867"
                          id="aspace_ref13_c1"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_a15dc838b4f54fd4549fcaf9f876a9a8">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Four manuscripts of Napoleon, three of which are signed, dating from 1797 to 1803. The 29 prints portray Napoleon during this period of his career.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref14" level="item">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Vol. 3: Napoleon Bonaparte as Emperor: Portraits and Autographs</unittitle>
               <container altrender="Paige 15"
                          containerid="39002042582867"
                          id="aspace_ref14_c1"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_60ee8ae8dfba50e7d609980d5c5a7c73">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Five manuscripts, all signed by Napoleon, dated 1805 to 1810. There are 54 prints of the emperor.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref16" level="item">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Vol. 4: Napoleon Bonaparte in Exile: Portraits and Autographs</unittitle>
               <container altrender="Paige 15"
                          containerid="39002042582867"
                          id="aspace_ref16_c1"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_119180b1efd4a5d026f8350ddc106aad">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This volume contains three manuscripts from around 1817, all signed by Napoleon. There are also 25 documents signed by persons associated with Napoleon at St. Helena, and/or with the removal his body from St. Helena to Paris in 1840. These documents date from 1817 to 1840. The 48 prints in this volume include portraits of Napoleon in exile, portraits of those connected with him at this time, and scenic views.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref18" level="item">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Vol. 5: Napoleon's Generals and Marshals: Portraits and Autographs</unittitle>
               <container altrender="Paige 15"
                          containerid="39002042582867"
                          id="aspace_ref18_c1"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_2cb2f6f44432d6738f9c5e7b49b2fb38">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>There are 35 documents in this volume, each one signed by one of Napoleon's generals or marshals. These manuscripts date from 1795 to 1824. Each letter, with one exception, is accompanied by a contemporary portrait of the sender.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref20" level="item">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Vol. 6: Celebrities and Statesmen: Portraits and Autographs</unittitle>
               <container altrender="Paige 15"
                          containerid="39002042582875"
                          id="aspace_ref20_c1"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">2</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_51972d066dd80736105eb79e31d1640a">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This volume contains 33 documents of famous persons of the Napoleonic era. Included are letters signed by: Paul I of Russia, Alexander I of Russia, Frederic Auguste of Saxony, Francis II of Austria, Frederic William II of Prussia, Louis XVIII of France, Metternich, Pope Pius VII, Talleyrand, Wellington, and others. These letters range in date from 1776 to 1830. There are 36 prints portraying the important figures of this period.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref22" level="item">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Vol. 7: Napoleon's Family: Portraits and Autographs</unittitle>
               <container altrender="Paige 15"
                          containerid="39002042582875"
                          id="aspace_ref22_c1"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">2</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_c02aea102366702d5f2c5b840a684eb3">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The 22 documents contained in this volue are all signed by members of Napoleon's family. They are dated from 1774 to 1849. 26 prints portray the family.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref24" level="item">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Vol. 8: Josephine de Beauharnais, Empress and Queen: Portraits and Autographs</unittitle>
               <container altrender="Paige 15"
                          containerid="39002042582875"
                          id="aspace_ref24_c1"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">2</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_6111587e8bd440f81cb8787563f852b0">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This volume contains nine manuscripts signed by the empress Joesphine, dated from 1786 to 1812, and 25 portraits of her.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref26" level="item">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Vol. 9: Marie Louise and the King of Rome: Portraits and Autographs</unittitle>
               <container altrender="Paige 15"
                          containerid="39002042582875"
                          id="aspace_ref26_c1"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">2</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_d3b4c46bfa22005a7fe8ee56a2c0b177">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Six letters signed by Marie Louise and/or Napoleon II, King of Rome. Also present is the protestation of Marie Louise to the Congress of Vienna, in which she claims the French throne for her son. All documents are from the period 1810 to 1825. The 34 prints depict Marie louise and Napoleon II.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref28" level="item">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Vol. 10: Historical Scenes, Views: Allegorical and Caricatures</unittitle>
               <container altrender="Paige 15"
